# Ignore everything in this directory by default — `private/` is for
# local-only working notes (feature scoping, roadmap thinking,
# personal todo lists, draft docs that aren't ready for the public
# repo). Anything placed here stays on your machine.
#
# Two files are intentionally tracked: this `.gitignore` itself, and
# the `README.md` that documents the convention. Anything else is
# yours and stays local.
*
!.gitignore
!README.md
